SUMMARY:Deadline: Berlin Senate: Arbeitsstipendien Film/Video 2027\, Kuenst
 lerinnenfoerderung (Berlin-based women artists)
DESCRIPTION:Work stipends for women film and video artists under the Berlin
  Senate's Kuenstlerinnenfoerderung (women artists' funding program). ELIGI
 BILITY: women film and video artists based in Berlin. Deadline 1 October 2
 026\, 11:00 CEST\, per the Senate's official deadline calendar. NOTE: rese
 arch-sourced from the Senate deadline calendar\; the stipend amount was no
 t published there\, so confirm details on the Senate funding pages before 
 applying.\n\nOrganisation: Berlin Senate Department for Culture and Social
  Cohesion\nLocation: Berlin\, Germany. Women film and video artists based 
 in Berlin only.\nAward: Work stipend for women film and video artists\; th
 e amount for this round is not yet confirmed (sibling Senate work stipends
  pay EUR 2\,000 per month). No application fee.\nDuration: Work stipend fo
 r 2027\n\nMore: https://www.berlin.de/sen/kultur/foerderung/antragsfristen
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.berlin.de/sen/kultur/foerderung/antragsfristen/?utm_source=
 artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany. Women film and video artists based in Berlin onl
 y.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fondazione-prada-film-fund-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T104504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260806
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260807
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fondazione Prada Film Fund 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Fondazione Prada Film Fund is an annual EUR 1.5 million fun
 d backing 10 to 12 feature-length films (fiction\, documentary\, and anima
 tion\, 65 minutes or longer) across development\, production\, and post-pr
 oduction. ELIGIBILITY: independent producers and production companies with
  a track record (approximately two or more feature films premiered at majo
 r international festivals) and partial financing already secured\; this is
  aimed at established independent producers\, NOT individual emerging arti
 sts. DEADLINES: 6 August 2026 for projects in production\; 10 September 20
 26 for development and post-production projects (this card uses the earlie
 st deadline). Apply via the Fondazione Prada Film Fund page. NOTE: the fun
 der's primary page was not directly reachable at time of entry\; dates cor
 roborated via industry trade press (Screen\, Cineuropa). Verify the exact 
 track deadline before applying.\n\nOrganisation: Fondazione Prada\nLocatio
 n: Milan\, Italy-based fund\; open worldwide to independent producers and 
 production companies.\nAward: EUR 1.5 million total pool supporting 10 to 
 12 feature films. Development grants EUR 15\,000 to 80\,000\; production g
 rants EUR 30\,000 to 250\,000\; post-production grants EUR 40\,000 to 100\
 ,000. No application fee.\nDuration: Feature film funding (development\, p
 roduction\, or post-production)\n\nMore: https://www.fondazioneprada.org/f
 ilm-fund/?lang=en&utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referra
 l
URL:https://www.fondazioneprada.org/film-fund/?lang=en&utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Milan\, Italy-based fund\; open worldwide to independent producers
  and production companies.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:guardian-arte-democracy-at-stake-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T104504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260914
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260915
SUMMARY:Deadline: Democracy at Stake in Europe: Short Documentary Fund
DESCRIPTION:Guardian Documentaries and arte.tv have opened a short document
 ary film fund on the theme 'Democracy at Stake in Europe'\, supporting the
  development and production of a character-led documentary short exploring
  threats\, pressures and challenges facing democratic societies across Eur
 ope. The aim is to amplify personal stories that help audiences understand
  democracy in Europe today and to stimulate public debate\; suggested area
 s of focus include press freedom\, civic trust and democratic participatio
 n. AWARD: one project receives GBP 10\,000 in production support\; alongsi
 de the financial award\, the selected filmmaker receives editorial and cre
 ative input from the partners\, with distribution through Guardian and art
 e.tv platforms. The funding can be used for work linked to the film's deve
 lopment and production\, such as research\, filming and post-production\, 
 subject to the applicant's proposed budget and plan. ELIGIBILITY: open to 
 European filmmakers aged 18 or over\; the call is focused on a single shor
 t documentary and is intended for projects where individual experience and
  perspective are central to telling a wider story about democratic life in
  Europe. Deadline 14 September 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Guardian Documentari
 es and arte.tv\nLocation: Europe.\nAward: GBP 10\,000 in production suppor
 t for one short documentary project\, plus editorial and creative input fr
 om the partners and distribution through Guardian and arte.tv platforms.\n
 Duration: Development and production of a single short documentary.\n\nMor
 e: https://vibrantshropshire.co.uk/funding/democracy-at-stake-in-europe/?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://vibrantshropshire.co.uk/funding/democracy-at-stake-in-europe/?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Europe.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:circle-expanded-orbit-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T104504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260709
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260710
SUMMARY:Deadline: CIRCLE Expanded Orbit 1st Edition
DESCRIPTION:CIRCLE Expanded Orbit is the first edition of an international 
 training programme dedicated to immersive storytelling and XR-based practi
 ces\, run by the CIRCLE Training Initiative in partnership with Onassis ON
 X. It supports women and gender-expansive filmmakers\, artists\, XR creato
 rs\, and multidisciplinary storytellers working across XR\, MR\, VR\, AR\,
  AI\, and game-based narratives\, with no prior XR experience required. Se
 lected individuals or teams of up to two receive individual mentorship\, g
 roup sessions\, co-creation workshops\, and structured feedback\, plus acc
 ess to an international network of professionals. The in-person training t
 akes place from November 21 to 26\, 2026\, in Athens\, Greece. Applicants 
 should be developing a project with a strong artistic vision and clear int
 erest in immersive formats\, ideally with a producer attached and partial 
 budget secured. A participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per person applies\, wit
 h scholarships of up to 50 percent available based on financial need.\n\nO
 rganisation: CIRCLE Training Initiative (with Onassis ONX)\nLocation: Athe
 ns\, Greece\nAward: No cash stipend. Provides individual mentorship from w
 orld-leading experts\, group sessions\, co-creation workshops\, structured
  feedback\, and access to an international professional network across fil
 m\, art\, design\, and technology. Participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per per
 son (EUR 4\,000 per team of two)\, with scholarships covering up to 50 per
 cent available for those with financial need. EUR 2\,000 participation fee
  per person (EUR 4\,000 per team of two)\; up to 50 percent scholarships a
 vailable\nDuration: 6 days (in-person training)\n\nMore: https://www.docci
 rcle.me/expanded-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=re
 ferral
URL:https://www.doccircle.me/expanded-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Athens\, Greece
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:circle-fiction-orbit-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260713T104504Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260710
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260711
SUMMARY:Deadline: CIRCLE Fiction Orbit 3rd Edition
DESCRIPTION:CIRCLE Fiction Orbit is a one-week retreat in Herceg Novi\, Mon
 tenegro for up to six fiction feature film projects led by teams of women 
 and gender-expansive filmmakers developing their second\, third\, or fourt
 h narrative feature. Participants work with leading experts on script deve
 lopment\, legal and production strategy\, career positioning\, and receive
  psychological support throughout the creative process. Applicants must id
 entify as a woman or gender-expansive filmmaker\, work as a screenwriter\,
  director\, or producer\, have completed at least one feature\, and submit
  a project with a producer attached. Accommodation and meals are provided\
 , but travel is not covered\, and a participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per pe
 rson applies. At least one 50 percent scholarship is available annually fo
 r those with demonstrated financial need. The third edition runs October 2
 5 to November 1\, 2026\, with applications due July 10\, 2026.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: CIRCLE Training Initiative\nLocation: Herceg Novi\, Montenegro\nAwar
 d: Accommodation and meals provided\; in-depth script consultations\, lega
 l and production strategy guidance\, career development mentorship\, and p
 sychological support. Travel not covered. Participation fee of EUR 2\,000 
 per person applies. At least one 50 percent scholarship available annually
  for participants from lower-income countries\, those without national fun
 ding\, or with demonstrated financial need. EUR 2\,000 participation fee (
 accommodation and meals included\; travel not covered)\; 50 percent schola
 rship available for demonstrated need\nDuration: One week\n\nMore: https:/
 /www.doccircle.me/fiction-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
URL:https://www.doccircle.me/fiction-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Herceg Novi\, Montenegro
END:VEVENT
